Valter ROS demo

1) Turn on WiFi "valterstation2.4GHz"
2) Turn on Valter
   (otional) 2.1) ping 192.168.101.101
   (otional) 2.2) ssh 192.168.101.101
3) valter1 (ssh 192.168.101.101)
   3.1) sudo hciconfig hci0 piscan
	    (reminder) 3.0) cat ~/.bashrc
	    (otional)  3.10) cd ~/git/valter/software/ros/workspaces/valter1
	    (otional)  3.20) source devel/setup.sh
4) ROS master (ROS_MASTER_URI=http://192.168.0.100:11311)
   (reminder) 4.0) cat ~/.bashrc
   (otional)  4.10) cd ~/git/valter/software/ros/workspaces/master
   (otional)  4.20) source devel/setup.sh
 5) ROS master (ROS_MASTER_URI=http://192.168.0.100:11311)
   5.10) roscore
   (manual action) 5.19) connect USB joystick
   5.20) rosrun joy joy_node
   (optional) 5.30) rqt_graph
   5.40) rosrun valter valter_joy_teleop_cmd_vel_pub
6) valter1 (ssh 192.168.101.101)
   6.10) rosrun valter cmd_vel_subscriber
7) Launch expclient 
   7.0.0) (not from Qt) cd /home/maska/git/valter/software/computer/client/qt/build-expclient-Desktop_Qt_5_7_0_GCC_64bit-Debug
   7.0.0) ./expclient wlan0
   7.1.0) (from Qt)  Disable 192.168.0.* (wired interdafce)
   7.10) (TCP Interface) -> set Central Host IP Address (Valter workshop 192.168.101.100)
   7.20) (TCP Interface) -> press button "Update Settings / Connect All"
   7.30) (TCP Interface) -> Control Mode column -> Uncheck All except [PLATFORM-CONTROL-P1]
   7.40) (TCP Interface) -> press button "Disconnect All"
   7.50) (TCP Interface) -> press button "Update Settings / Connect All"
   7.51) Enable back 192.168.0.* (wired interface)
   

   
   
KNOWN PROBLEMS

https://www.bitpi.co/2015/02/11/how-to-change-raspberry-pis-swapfile-size-on-rasbian/
[
sudo nano /etc/dphys-swapfile
The default value in Raspbian is:

CONF_SWAPSIZE=100
We will need to change this to:

CONF_SWAPSIZE=1024
Then you will need to stop and start the service that manages the swapfile own Rasbian:

sudo /etc/init.d/dphys-swapfile stop
sudo /etc/init.d/dphys-swapfile start
You can then verify the amount of memory + swap by issuing the following command:

free -m
The output should look like:

total     used     free   shared  buffers   cached
Mem:           435       56      379        0        3       16
-/+ buffers/cache:       35      399
Swap:         1023        0     1023
]
   
